# Environment Configuration

## Development Environment

Copy this file to `.env` and update with your actual values:

```env
# API Configuration
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api

# For production use:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api

# Firebase Configuration (if using)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_key
# EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_domain
# EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id

# Feature Flags
EXPO_PUBLIC_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=true
EXPO_PUBLIC_ENABLE_CRASH_REPORTING=true
```

## Local Development

For local development, use:
```env
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:8080/api
```

(10.0.2.2 is the special alias for localhost on Android emulator)

For iOS simulator:
```env
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
```

## Production

Always use HTTPS for production API endpoints:
```env
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.tutorfinder.com/api
```

## Notes

- Never commit `.env` file with sensitive credentials
- Use environment-specific `.env.local`, `.env.staging`, `.env.production`
- Keep `.env.example` in version control as a template
